            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "New `vim.async` should address this as task errors propagate upwards. In older versions errors were only propagated when a task was joined/awaited (which nvim-treesitter isn't doing).\n\nFWIW I don't think there's an actual problem here. The errors vim.uv.spawn issues are only due to improper inputs (bad cmd or cwd). If they are ok, then the spawn will succeed and the exit code will be returned in the callback.\n\nWhether exit codes should be treated as errors or not is a different question. Python has various versions of subprocess (popen, run, call, check_call) to provide convenience wrappers for all the different use cases. `vim.system` probably maps closest to `popen`.",
